      <prefercite id="aspace_83873fdb417967e2ac486f95b04059a7">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>French Miscellaneous Manuscripts Collection. Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_29661a98d87499f1a638da1cc09f37ee">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>An artificial collection of correspondence, manuscripts, volumes, and miscellanea relating to France, 1115-1941.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_c26cf9b0ea38f5adb2b2b0b13f6d42f7">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The papers are arranged in four sections: volumes, correspondence and loose papers, miscellaneous, and oversize. All items that are not listed individually in this register--and this is the vast majority of the papers in the collection--are filed as "correspondence and loose papers in boxes 7-8. Most items are cataloged individually in the manuscript catalog, the union catalog, and the inventory catalog.</p>  
      </arrangement>
